Explain the difference between the == operator and the === operator.
The difference between the == operator and the === oprator is that 
the === operator checks if two values are equal without taking automatic type conversions into account, 
while the == operator does take the automatic type conversions into account.

Explain what a closure is.
A closure is a function that enables you to acces a variable 
that was first initiated as a local variable by an instance of a specific function call.
The enclosing function enables you to reference a local variable even after the function it was first created in is called mutiple times.

Explain what higher order functions are.
Higher order functions are functions that operate with other functions, by taking them as arguments of using them are return value.

Explain what a query selector is and give an example line of JavaScript that uses a query selector.
A query selector is a selector, that marks elements to which a set of styles apply to, that you want to search for. 
It can be used to search for certain elements with idential styles.

